DON'T DO IT.  This is my second time ordering from this place. I ordered a half fried chicken with pork fried rice. My partner ordered spare ribs with special fried rice. ​  The fried rice is very dry. It tasted like it has been laying around the kitchen for days and re-fried. The fried chicken is also dry. The meat has a strong fridge smell. I don't know how many times the chicken was fried before giving to us. And the spare ribs are extremely salty and taste like they will go bad in a few more hours..., ​and they cost up to almost 35$. This is Chinese food in Washington​ Heights​.  I am Chinese, and my partner is Cuban​ American​. ​This place gave out food that was​ not even close to "just taste ok." While I am writing this review, my stomach is hurting at the same time. I will file for a lawsuit​ against them if I have any health issues in the following days. The below part is for the restaurant to read. (if they would care to read the review on sites)  开饭店做生意，赚钱还是要有良心。请你们在把饭钱放进外卖盒之前自己先尝一下，我们花了近35美刀叫来的却是过夜的饭菜，几近变质的食物，有没有考虑一下我们消费者的感受？希望你们能好好反省一下。

This place is like a Chinese restaurant out of a 1950s Caribbean town, so if you're looking for a genuine vintage experience in NYC, look no further. The menu is split half-half between the Chinese and Latin American cuisines, so there's no fusion between the two. I had the Chicharrones de pollo, which was a tasty and huge serving of homemade fried chicken, with a side of the most delicious sweet plantains I've had in a long long time. They gave me 8 whole pieces of chicken for a measly $11, there was so much of it that I ended up taking home half of it. Anyway, I'd be glad to come back anytime, really tasty and good value.
